Edna MAGONIGLE, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Margaret A. JAMISON and Martha A. Jamison, Individually and as Copartners Doing Business under the Firm Name and Style of Jay Street Terminal, Defendants-Appellees. No. 205. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 3, 1941. Leon A. Fischel, of New York City (Arthur N. Blair, of Brooklyn, N. Y., of counsel), for appellant. Daniel Miner, of New York City (Clarence S. Zipp and William S. O’Connor, both of New York City, of counsel), for appel-lees.

Before SWAN, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed on the authority of Garthe v. Ruppert, 264 N.Y. 290, 190 N.E. 643.
